    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Language server\n\n_No response_\n\n### Requested feature\n\nIt'd be nice if we can configure the `root_files` of LSP servers via `.setup()`:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/blob/f3195835c0447ee2c80152b893ab51ca162b04a9/lua/lspconfig/server_configurations/lua_ls.lua#L3-L11\r\n\r\nIt might be a tricky to implement though, since we need to make sure that the `root_dir` function refers to the same table when it was defined. Any ideas?\n\n### Other clients which have this feature\n\n_No response_",
    "closed_at": "2023-09-19T12:10:16Z",
